### [UX-004] `ToolCard` header uses `<div onClick>` instead of `<button>` — not keyboard accessible
- **Heuristic:** #4 Consistency and Standards / WCAG 4.1.2
- **Apps:** Both — sarah-practice-plan (`JungleTools.jsx` equivalent) and music-chart/src/components/ToolCard.jsx line 11
- **Location:** `music-chart/src/components/ToolCard.jsx` line 11
- **Issue:** The collapsible `ToolCard` header that expands and collapses each tool panel is implemented as `<div onClick={...}>`. This is not reachable by keyboard (no tab stop), is not announced as a button to screen readers, and has no `aria-expanded` state. There are approximately 12 ToolCard instances in the Tools tab of sarah-practice-plan alone.
- **Impact:** Keyboard users cannot open any tool. Screen reader users receive no indication that a section is expandable or what its current state is.
- **Fix:**
  ```jsx
  <button
    onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}
    aria-expanded={open}
    style={{ /* existing styles + width: "100%", text-align: left */ }}
  >
  ```
  Add `role="region"` and `aria-labelledby` to the collapsible content panel.

