### [UX-007] Flow Mode exit confirmation only works by pressing "Exit" — no keyboard Escape support, no focus trap
- **Heuristic:** #3 User Control and Freedom / WCAG 2.1 (Keyboard)
- **App:** sarah-practice-plan
- **Location:** `App.jsx` lines 1405–1441 (exit confirmation dialog in `FlowMode`)
- **Issue:** The exit confirmation modal is a `<div>` styled to look like a dialog. It has no `role="dialog"`, no `aria-modal="true"`, no `aria-labelledby`, and no focus trap. Focus is not moved into the modal when it opens. There is no `keydown` listener for the Escape key to cancel. The "Stay" / "Exit" buttons render in the modal but a keyboard user pressing Tab will continue to tab through the underlying Flow content behind the overlay rather than being contained in the modal.
- **Impact:** Screen reader users cannot interact with the confirmation dialog. Keyboard users who accidentally trigger exit have no way to recover without clicking.
- **Fix:** Add `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, an `aria-labelledby` pointing to the "Exit Flow?" heading, a `useEffect` that moves focus to the first button on open, and a `keydown` listener that calls `setShowExitConfirm(false)` on `Escape`.

