### [UX-008] BPM range input (`<input type="range">`) has no accessible label
- **Heuristic:** WCAG 1.3.1 Info and Relationships; 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value
- **Apps:** Both
- **Location:** `App.jsx` line 2291 (sarah-practice-plan MetronomePanel); `music-chart/src/tools/Metronome.jsx` line 471
- **Issue:** The main BPM slider renders as `<input type="range" min={40} max={280} value={metro.bpm} ...>` with no associated `<label>`, no `aria-label`, and no `aria-valuetext`. A screen reader announces the current value as a number with no context for what the number represents. The `accentColor` and `outline: "none"` suppress the browser's default focus indicator.
- **Impact:** Screen reader users hear "40" to "280" with no indication this is a BPM control. Users navigating by keyboard cannot see the focused state on the slider.
- **Fix:**
  ```jsx
  <input
    type="range"
    aria-label="Tempo in BPM"
    aria-valuetext={`${metro.bpm} BPM`}
    min={40} max={280}
    value={metro.bpm}
    ...
  />
  ```

