### [UX-009] Dark mode does not respect `prefers-color-scheme` system setting
- **Heuristic:** #2 Match Between System and Real World / User Expectation
- **Apps:** Both
- **Location:** `App.jsx` lines 4174–4181 (sarah-practice-plan); `music-chart/src/App.jsx` lines 23–29
- **Issue:** Both apps initialize theme from `localStorage.getItem("theme")`. If no value is saved, they default to light mode. Neither app checks `window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)")` for the system preference. Users who have their OS set to dark mode at night will open the app in light mode and have to manually toggle it every session until they explicitly save a preference.
- **Impact:** A practice app used in low-light environments (late-night sessions are common for musicians) will blast white at full brightness with no respect for the system setting.
- **Fix:**
  ```js
  const saved = localStorage.getItem("theme");
  const dark = saved === "dark" || (saved === null && window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)").matches);
  ```

---

### [UX-010] Progress rail dots in Flow Mode are 8–12px tap targets with no accessible label
- **Heuristic:** Mobile Usability / WCAG 2.5.5 Target Size
- **App:** sarah-practice-plan
- **Location:** `App.jsx` lines 706–720 (`FlowProgressRail`)
- **Issue:** Each exercise navigation dot is rendered as a `<button>` with `width: isCurrent ? 12 : 8` and `height: isCurrent ? 12 : 8` with `padding: 0`. These are 8px–12px tap targets against the WCAG 2.5.5 recommended 44px minimum. The `title={ex.title}` attribute provides a tooltip on hover (desktop), but on mobile there is no accessible name at all announced to screen readers, and the tap target is approximately 1/5 the minimum recommended size. For a 15-exercise set, users must precisely hit a circle smaller than a grain of rice.
- **Impact:** Users miss taps repeatedly, jumping to wrong exercises. The feature is effectively unusable for motor-impaired users.
- **Fix:** Maintain the small visual dot inside a larger transparent hit area:
  ```jsx
  <button
    style={{ width: 44, height: 44, display: "flex", alignItems: "center", justifyContent: "center",
             background: "transparent", border: "none", padding: 0, cursor: "pointer" }}
    aria-label={`Go to exercise ${i + 1}: ${ex.title}`}
    aria-current={isCurrent ? "step" : undefined}
    onClick={() => onJump(i)}
  >
    <div style={{ width: size, height: size, borderRadius: "50%", /* existing visual styles */ }} />
  </button>
  ```

