### [UX-011] `<link>` tag for Google Fonts rendered inside the React component tree, not in `<head>`
- **Heuristic:** #1 Visibility of System Status (perceived performance)
- **Apps:** Both
- **Location:** `sarah-practice-plan/src/App.jsx` line 4793; `music-chart/src/App.jsx` line 239
- **Issue:** Both apps render `<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/...">` as a child of the root `<div>`. React renders this into the body, not the `<head>`. Browsers handle this inconsistently — some will apply it, but the font is loaded late in the rendering cycle, causing a flash of unstyled text (FOUT) with the system fallback (`-apple-system`, `Segoe UI`, etc.) before Playfair Display and Lato load. The fonts are declared as high-priority in `index.css` via `@import` already, so this `<link>` tag is redundant and potentially causes a double-load.
- **Impact:** Users see a brief layout shift as Playfair Display (a large serif) loads in — the 44px header text reflows noticeably. On slow connections this can take 2–3 seconds.
- **Fix:** Remove the `<link>` tags from the component render and rely solely on the `@import` in `index.css`, or move them into `index.html`'s `<head>` with `rel="preload"`.

