### [UX-012] "Backing Track Links" tool shows bare YouTube URLs as unclickable text
- **Heuristic:** #6 Recognition Rather Than Recall
- **App:** sarah-practice-plan
- **Location:** `App.jsx` lines 4687–4706
- **Issue:** The "Backing Track Links" ToolCard renders a list like `{ label: "Surf Rock 120 BPM", url: "youtube.com/watch?v=AEf8LF4Xu18" }` where the URL is displayed as non-linked text (a `<span>`). The URL is not prefixed with `https://` and is not wrapped in `<a>`. Users who want to open the link must manually copy-paste it and prepend the protocol. This is particularly painful on mobile where there is no keyboard copy shortcut.
- **Impact:** A feature intended to provide quick access to backing tracks becomes a friction point requiring manual URL entry.
- **Fix:** Either make these clickable links with `href={"https://" + l.url}` and `target="_blank" rel="noopener"`, or better yet, integrate these URLs directly into the Backing Tracks audio player that already exists in the same tab.

