## Accessibility Issues

### [A11Y-001] No semantic heading hierarchy — entire app uses styled `<div>` elements
- **WCAG:** 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)
- **Apps:** Both
- **Issue:** All section titles, level names, exercise titles, and page headings are `<div>` elements with font styling. Not a single `<h1>`, `<h2>`, or `<h3>` appears in App.jsx or music-chart/src/App.jsx. Screen reader users relying on heading navigation (a primary skip-navigation technique) find a completely flat document with no landmarks.
- **Fix:** Map the visual hierarchy to semantic headings. The app title ("Practice Plan") should be `<h1>`. Tab section titles ("Skills", "Tools") should be `<h2>`. Level names should be `<h3>`. Exercise titles in Flow Mode should be `<h2>` (as they are the primary page content).

### [A11Y-002] No skip-navigation link
- **WCAG:** 2.4.1 Bypass Blocks (Level A)
- **Apps:** Both
- **Issue:** There is no "Skip to main content" link. On the Practice tab, a keyboard user must tab through the full header, all 7 day-pill buttons, before reaching any exercise content.
- **Fix:** Add a visually-hidden-until-focused link as the first element in the DOM: `<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>`.

### [A11Y-003] Confetti animation on exercise completion uses `disableForReducedMotion: true` — but the audio chime still plays
- **WCAG:** 2.3.3 Animation from Interactions (Level AAA — but worth noting)
- **App:** sarah-practice-plan
- **Location:** `App.jsx` lines 4323–4333
- **Issue:** The confetti correctly passes `disableForReducedMotion: true` to the canvas-confetti library. However, the audio completion chime at lines 4307–4317 (PolySynth C major chord) fires unconditionally. For users with sensory sensitivities who have reduced motion enabled, unexpected audio surprises can be equally disorienting.
- **Note:** This is Level AAA and may be intentional — the audio feedback IS valuable for practice. The point is the reduced-motion check is incomplete if the goal is to be fully respectful of that preference.

### [A11Y-004] Color contrast — `T.textMuted` (#b8b2ab) on white background fails WCAG AA
- **WCAG:** 1.4.3 Contrast (Level AA) — minimum 4.5:1 for normal text
- **Apps:** Both
- **Issue:** The light theme defines `textMuted: "#b8b2ab"` against `bg: "#ffffff"`. The contrast ratio is approximately 2.8:1, well below the 4.5:1 minimum for normal text. This color is used extensively for secondary labels, status text, BPM "unit" labels, navigation inactive state, and timestamps.
- **Additionally:** `textLight: "#8c867f"` on white gives approximately 3.6:1 — still below AA for text smaller than 18px bold or 24px regular.
- **Fix:** Darken `textMuted` to approximately `#767069` (4.5:1 on white) and `textLight` to `#6b6560`.

### [A11Y-005] Interactive SVG dots and decorative SVGs lack `aria-hidden`
- **WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value
- **Apps:** Both
- **Issue:** Decorative SVGs such as the grid pattern background in MetronomePanel (`App.jsx` line 2271–2276) and the chevron arrows in FlowStepView (lines 746, 756) are rendered inline. Without `aria-hidden="true"`, screen readers attempt to read these SVGs and may announce "circle" or "path" elements.
- **Fix:** Add `aria-hidden="true"` to all decorative SVGs. For the functional chevron in ToolCard (`music-chart/src/components/ToolCard.jsx` line 19), use `aria-hidden="true"` since the button already has a text label.

### [A11Y-006] `<pre>` block for guitar tabs has no horizontal scroll announcement for screen readers
- **WCAG:** 1.3.1 Info and Relationships
- **App:** sarah-practice-plan
- **Location:** `App.jsx` line 1143 (TAB_CONTENT pre block)
- **Issue:** The guitar tabs displayed in a `<pre>` with `overflowX: "auto"` can extend 60–80 characters wide. There is no `role="region"`, `aria-label`, or announcement that the content scrolls horizontally.
- **Fix:** Add `role="region" aria-label="Guitar tab notation — scrollable"` and ensure the `<pre>` has `tabindex="0"` so keyboard users can focus and scroll it.

### [A11Y-007] `ReviewCheckIn` expand/collapse is a `<div onClick>` — same pattern as ToolCard
- **WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value
- **App:** sarah-practice-plan
- **Location:** `App.jsx` lines 654–675
- **Issue:** The `ReviewCheckIn` component renders a `<div onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}>` with no `role`, no `aria-expanded`, and no `tabindex`. The expand/collapse state is communicated only by the `▾` / `▸` characters.
- **Fix:** Replace the outer `<div>` with `<button>`, add `aria-expanded={open}`, and use `aria-label="Review check-in, tap to expand"`.

### [A11Y-008] Timer ring SVG has no accessible live region announcement
- **WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages
- **App:** sarah-practice-plan
- **Location:** `App.jsx` lines 523–541 (`TimerRing`)
- **Issue:** When the practice timer completes (`done ? "✓" : fmt`), the status change from time remaining to a checkmark is visible but never announced to screen readers. There is no `aria-live="polite"` region or `role="timer"`.
- **Fix:** Add `role="timer"` and `aria-live="polite"` to the inner time display div, and `aria-label={done ? "Timer complete" : `${fmt} remaining`}`.

