## Recommendations

### Priority 1 — Quick wins with high impact (1–2 hours each)
1. Add `aria-current="page"` and `aria-label` to all bottom nav buttons in both apps (UX-001).
2. Replace `outline: none` with `button:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid #d4a373; }` in both `index.css` files (UX-002).
3. Wrap the ToolCard `<div onClick>` in a `<button>` with `aria-expanded` (UX-004).
4. Add `aria-label` and `aria-valuetext` to all BPM sliders (UX-008).
5. Fix the system dark mode preference detection in both App.jsx init functions (UX-009).
6. Move the Google Fonts `<link>` tags out of the React component tree into `index.html` (UX-011).

### Priority 2 — Interaction improvements (half-day each)
7. Increase tap targets for Flow Mode progress rail dots to 44px hit area (UX-010).
8. Add heading semantics (`<h1>`, `<h2>`, `<h3>`) throughout both apps (A11Y-001).
9. Add `role="dialog"`, focus trap, and Escape key handler to the Flow Mode exit confirmation (UX-007).
10. Make Backing Track Links into actual clickable `<a>` elements with `https://` prefix (UX-012).

### Priority 3 — Structural improvements (1+ day each)
11. Add a loading state for Tone.js Sampler initialization so users know when the metronome sound is ready (UX-005).
12. Add error UI for microphone permission denial in LivePitchDetector and AudioRecorder.
13. Add `touch-action: pan-y` to Flow Mode container to prevent iOS back-swipe conflicts (UX-003).
14. Fix the skill sub-tabs overflow on narrow screens using the existing `hide-scrollbar` pattern (UX-006).
15. Darken `textMuted` and `textLight` to meet WCAG 4.5:1 contrast ratio (A11Y-004).

